  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nAnvil\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nanvil 0.2.0 (11b08e9 2023-08-16T00:24:19.012904000Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nanvil --fork-url $ARB_RPC_URL --port 8545 --chain-id 42161\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Run `anvil --fork-url $ARB_RPC_URL --port 8545 --chain-id 42161` with arbitrum RPC url that supports archive node\r\n2. Try calling `eth_getCode` via curl\r\n```\r\ncurl http://127.0.0.1:8545 \\\r\n  -X POST \\\r\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\r\n  -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getCode\",\"params\": [\"0x912CE59144191C1204E64559FE8253a0e49E6548\", \"latest\"],\"id\":1}'\r\n```\r\n3. Result is `{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":\"0x\"}%  `\r\n\r\nHowever simply removing `--chain-id` in CLI gets around this issue and returns the correct bytecode. Also anvil fetches correct chainID from the RPC so looks like there are no negative effects from not specifying. Not sure if this behavior is intended.",
